'''Sofyan Amrabat''' ({{langx|ar|سفيان أمرابط}}, {{langx|ber|ⵙⵓⴼⵢⴰⵏ ⴰⵎⵕⴰⴱⵟ}}; born 21 August 1996) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Betis]], on loan from [[Süper Lig]] side [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

Amrabat is a graduate of [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]'s youth system. He made his first-team debut for the club in November 2014, and went on to make 54 appearances for them in total, before being signed by [[Feyenoord]] in 2017. One year later, he joined Belgian team [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], who loaned him to Italian club [[Hellas Verona FC|Hellas Verona]] in August 2019. Verona purchased him and immediately sold him to Fiorentina in January 2020. He joined [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on loan in September 2023, winning the [[FA Cup]].

Born in the Netherlands, Amrabat played youth international football for both the Netherlands and Morocco. He made his senior international debut for Morocco in March 2017, and has represented the country at two [[FIFA World Cup]]s and three [[Africa Cup of Nations]].

==Club career==
===Utrecht===
Amrabat joined [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]'s youth system in 2007 from [[HSV De Zuidvogels]].<ref name="earlycareer">{{cite news |title=Marokko-uitblinker Amrabat: van Ten Hag-wingback tot doelwit van Europese top |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/1057696/marokko-uitblinker-amrabat-van-ten-hag-wingback-tot-doelwit-van-europese-top.html |website=voetbalprimeur.nl |date=7 December 2022 |access-date=26 July 2023}}</ref> He made his first-team debut for Utrecht against [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on 2 November 2014.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Elf feiten over Sofyan Amrabat- Feyenoord.nl |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/elf-feiten-over-sofyan-amrabat |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231023031630/https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/elf-feiten-over-sofyan-amrabat |archive-date=2023-10-23 |access-date=2025-11-01 |language=nl}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===
Amrabat joined [[Feyenoord]] in the summer of 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-06-30 |title=Feyenoord troeft Ajax af in strijd om Amrabat |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2180709-feyenoord-troeft-ajax-af-in-strijd-om-amrabat |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=nos.nl |language=nl}}</ref> He signed a four-year contract and Utrecht received a transfer fee of €4 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-06-30 |title=Sofyan Amrabat voor vier miljoen naar Feyenoord |url=https://www.rtvutrecht.nl/sport/1635053/sofyan-amrabat-voor-vier-miljoen-naar-feyenoord |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.rtvutrecht.nl |language=nl}}</ref>

===Club Brugge===
In August 2018, he joined Belgian team [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] on a four-year contract, with Feyenoord receiving €2.5 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-08-24 |title=Feyenoord laat Amrabat met tegenzin naar Club Brugge gaan |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2247335-feyenoord-laat-amrabat-met-tegenzin-naar-club-brugge-gaan |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=nos.nl |language=nl}}</ref> He was sent on loan to Italian club [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] in August 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2019-08-22 |title=Club Brugge verhuurt Sofyan Amrabat aan Serie A-club Hellas Verona {{!}} Sportnieuws |url=https://sportnieuws.nl/voetbal/transfernieuws/club-brugge-verhuurt-sofyan-amrabat-aan-serie-a-club-hellas-verona/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231023031630/https://sportnieuws.nl/voetbal/transfernieuws/club-brugge-verhuurt-sofyan-amrabat-aan-serie-a-club-hellas-verona/ |archive-date=2023-10-23 |access-date=2025-11-01 |work=Sportnieuws |language=nl-NL}}</ref>

===Hellas Verona===
In January 2020, Hellas Verona exercised their option to purchase Amrabat from Club Brugge for €3.5 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-01-31 |title=UPDATE - officieel: Hellas Verona licht de aankoopoptie van Amrabat en maakt meteen winst |url=https://www.voetbalkrant.com/nieuws/2020-01-31/-sofyan-amrabat-speelt-vanaf-zomer-bij-fiorentina |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=Voetbalkrant.com |language=nl}}</ref> They immediately sold him to [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] for a transfer fee of €20 million, with the deal containing potential add-ons of €1.5 million.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eurosport.it/calcio/serie-a/2018-2019/fiorentina-ecco-per-amrabat-in-estate-napoli-beffato-al-verona-20-milioni_sto7644550/story.shtml |title=FIORENTINA, ECCO PER AMRABAT IN ESTATE: NAPOLI BEFFATO, AL VERONA 20 MILIONI |website=eurosport.it |date=31 January 2020 |access-date=28 July 2023}}</ref> Amrabat remained on loan at Hellas Verona until the end of the 2019–20 season, as he was not permitted to play for more than two clubs during the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-01-31 |title=Huizer profvoetballer Sofyan Amrabat maakt miljoenentransfer naar Fiorentina |url=https://www.noordhollandsdagblad.nl/incoming/huizer-profvoetballer-sofyan-amrabat-maakt-miljoenentransfer-naar-fiorentina/10919037.html |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=Noordhollands Dagblad |language=nl-NL}}</ref> In July 2020, he won Hellas Verona's Player of the Season award.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-07-31 |title=Amrabat neemt met ereprijs afscheid bij Hellas Verona |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/amrabat-neemt-met-ereprijs-afscheid-bij-hellas-verona |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=vi.nl |language=nl-NL}}</ref>

===Fiorentina===
Amrabat made his debut for Fiorentina in a 4–3 loss to [[Inter Milan]] on 26 September 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tito |first=The |date=2020-09-26 |title=Inter Milan 4-3 Fiorentina: Highlights |url=https://www.violanation.com/2020/9/26/21457535/inter-milan-4-3-fiorentina-goals-kouame-martinez-ceccherini-castrovilli-chiesa-lukaku-dambrosio |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=Viola Nation |language=en-US}}</ref> He started and played every minute of Fiorentina's 2–1 defeat to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in the [[2023 UEFA Europa Conference League final]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65826820 |title=Fiorentina 1–2 West Ham United |website=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2023 |access-date=9 August 2023}}</ref>

====Loan to Manchester United====
Amrabat joined [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on loan from Fiorentina on 1 September 2023, on a deadline day until the end of the 2023–24 season. Manchester United paid Fiorentina a loan fee of £8.5 million, with the deal containing an option to buy for £21.4 million.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Sofyan Amrabat: Manchester United sign midfielder from Fiorentina on loan with £21.4m option to buy |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/32461/12952503/sofyan-amrabat-manchester-united-sign-midfielder-from-fiorentina-on-loan-with-21-4m-option-to-buy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127120853/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/32461/12952503/sofyan-amrabat-manchester-united-sign-midfielder-from-fiorentina-on-loan-with-21-4m-option-to-buy |archive-date=2024-11-27 |access-date=2025-11-01 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=United complete loan move for Amrabat |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/sofyan-amrabat-joins-man-utd-on-loan-from-fiorentina |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.manutd.com |language=en}}</ref> On 23 September, he made his [[Premier League]] debut, coming off the bench in the 89th minute replacing [[Jonny Evans]], in a 1–0 away win over [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lisle |first=Tim de |date=2023-09-23 |title=Burnley 0-1 Manchester United: Premier League – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/sep/23/burnley-v-manchester-united-premier-league-live-updates |access-date=2025-11-01 |work=the Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Three days later, Amrabat made his first start for the ''Red Devils'', in a 3–0 victory over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in the [[EFL Cup|Carabao Cup]] [[2023–24 EFL Cup#Third round|third round]] at [[Old Trafford]] where he played 60 minutes before being replaced by debutant [[Dan Gore]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-01 |title=Sofyan Amrabat oozes class for Manchester United in 3-0 win against Crystal Palace |url=https://onefootball.com/pt-br/noticias/sofyan-amrabat-oozes-class-for-manchester-united-in-3-0-win-against-crystal-palace-38287292 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=OneFootball |language=pt-br}}</ref> On 1 November 2023, Amrabat was nominated for the 2023 [[African Footballer of the Year]] by [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-11 |title=CAF announces CAF Awards 2023 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-caf-awards-2023-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=2023-11-01 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Amrabat became the first Moroccan player to win the [[FA Cup]] after United beat [[Manchester City]] in the [[2024 FA Cup final]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/05/362873/man-uniteds-sofyan-amrabat-is-first-moroccan-to-win-fa-cup|title=Man United's Sofyan Amrabat Is First Moroccan to Win FA Cup|date=25 May 2024|access-date=24 January 2025|work=[[Morocco World News]]|location=[[Rabat]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240809095312/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/05/362873/man-uniteds-sofyan-amrabat-is-first-moroccan-to-win-fa-cup|archive-date=9 August 2024|url-status=live|last=Rahhou|first=Jihane}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 30 August 2024, [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] announced that they had reached an agreement to sign Amrabat on loan for the 2024–25 season, with an obligation to buy for €12 million after the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=SPORTS |first=beIN |date=2024-08-30 |title=Fenerbahçe transferi KAP a bildirdi Amrabat formayı giydi |url=https://beinsports.com.tr/haber/fenerbahce-transferi-kapa-bildirdi |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=beinsports.com.tr |language=tr-TR}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the team in a away match against [[Trabzonspor]] on the last minute, helping his team achieve a victory. The transfer became permanent on 1 July 2025.

==== Loan to Betis ====
On 1 September 2025, Amrabat was loaned to [[Real Betis]] without a buy option due to Fenerbahçe recently buying the player.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transfer Bilgilendirme |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/transfer-bilgilendirme |date= 2025-09-01 |access-date=2025-09-01 |website=www.Fenerbahçe SK |language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
===Netherlands under-15 team===
Amrabat was eligible to represent the Netherlands or Morocco at international level.<ref>{{cite news |title=Amrabat's stellar World Cup backs up Morocco choice |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/sofyan-amrabat-morocco-journey-qatar-2022-fifa-world-cup |website=fifa.com |date=16 December 2022 |access-date=26 July 2023}}</ref> At first, he represented the Netherlands,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Taylor |first=Daniel |date=2023-03-06 |title=Sofyan Amrabat: His 'perfect' tackle on Mbappe and learning from Ten Hag |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4274906/2023/03/06/amrabat-mbappe-ten-hag/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> making four appearances at under-15 level.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Turkije O15 - Nederland O15 |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185192/uitslagen/wedstrijd/16802 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Nederland O15 - Slowakije O15 |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185192/uitslagen/wedstrijd/17134 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Nederland O15 - Slowakije O15 |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185192/uitslagen/wedstrijd/17138 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.onsoranje.nl}}</ref>

===Morocco===
Amrabat was selected in the [[Morocco national under-17 football team|Morocco under-17 national team]] for the [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fédération Internationale de Football Association. |url=http://www.fifadata.com/document/FU17/2013/pdf/FU17_2013_SquadLists.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101115412/http://www.fifadata.com/document/FU17/2013/pdf/FU17_2013_SquadLists.pdf |archive-date=2013-11-01 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.fifadata.com}}</ref> He made three appearances at the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |title=All Sofyan Amrabat's games and results  {{!}} BeSoccer |url=https://www.besoccer.com/player/matches/s-amrabat-197959 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240515050102/https://www.besoccer.com/player/matches/s-amrabat-197959 |archive-date=2024-05-15 |access-date=2025-11-01 |language=en}}</ref> On 28 March 2017, Amrabat made his senior debut for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] in a 1–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] win over [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bakkali |first=Achraf |title=Première apparition de Sofyan Amrabat avec les Lions de l'Atlas |url=http://mountakhab.net/www/modules/article_une/index.php?storyid=469107 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401144914/http://mountakhab.net/www/modules/article_une/index.php?storyid=469107 |archive-date=2017-04-01 |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=Mountakhab.net |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Sofyan Amrabat maakt Marokko-debuut |url=https://www.fcutrecht.nl/nieuws/2017/03/sofyan-amrabat-maakt-marokko-debuut/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=FC Utrecht}}</ref> In May 2018, he was named in Morocco's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-05-17 |title=World Cup 2018: Youssef En Nesyri replaces Badr Benoun in Morocco final squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44160388 |access-date=2025-11-01 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 10 November 2022, Amrabat was named in Morocco's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-11 |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad, predicted line-up versus France and star players {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2022-11-10 |title=S8 |url=https://s8.com.co/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> As Morocco clinched 4th place in the tournament, his strong performances led to an increase of interest for his services across Europe.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-06 |title=Opinion: Sofyan Amrabat proves vs Spain why Tottenham must sign him |url=https://www.hitc.com/opinion-sofyan-amrabat-proves-vs-spain-why-tottenham-must-sign-him/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=www.hitc.com |language=en-GB}}</ref> Amrabat appeared for Morocco at the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] where he was sent off in the 83rd minute of the team's 2–0 loss to [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=South Africa stun Morocco to book quarter-final ticket |url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/south-africa-stun-morocco-to-book-quarter-final-ticket/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |website=South Africa stun Morocco to book quarter-final ticket |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Amrabat was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Amrabat was born in [[Huizen]] in the Netherlands,<ref name="earlycareer"/> to parents of [[Rifians|Moroccan-Riffian]] descent.<ref>{{cite news |title=One on one: Sofyan Amrabat |url=https://www.acffiorentina.com/en/news/all/news-men-first-team/2021-02-10/one-on-one-sofyan-amrabat |website=acffiorentina.com |date=10 February 2021 |access-date=26 July 2023}}</ref> He is the younger brother of former Morocco international [[Nordin Amrabat]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-11 |title=Amrabat brother wants PSG move for Fiorentina midfielder - Football Italia |url=https://football-italia.net/amrabat-brother-wants-psg-move-for-fiorentina-midfielder/ |access-date=2025-11-01 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

